1
00:00:59,000 --> 00:00:59,880
Morphine 10.

2
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,680
Here.

3
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,480
Doctor,

4
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:15,560
save him.

5
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,760
Doctor, save him.

6
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:17,440
Hurry, save my brother.

7
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:18,280
What's wrong?

8
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:18,800
Doctor,

9
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:20,120
please save my brother.

10
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:20,680
Doctor,

11
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,039
please save him.

12
00:01:23,039 --> 00:01:23,600
Doctor,

13
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:24,530
hurry, save him.

14
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:28,300
Let me handle this.

15
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,490
Hurry, save my brother.

16
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:43,000
He's alive!

17
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,640
Thank you, Doctor.

18
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,400
You saved my brother!

19
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,880
Thank you for saving my husband.

20
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,280
You're a miracle worker.

21
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:52,960
Thank you.

22
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:53,759
You really are a miracle worker.

23
00:01:53,759 --> 00:01:54,600
You saved my brother.

24
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,640
Thank you, Doctor.

25
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,360
Thank you.

26
00:01:57,759 --> 00:01:58,280
Thank you.

27
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,340
Thank you, Doctor.

28
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,960
He died.

29
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,720
How is that possible?

30
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,160
Didn't we just save him yesterday?

31
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,820
What exactly did you give him?

32
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,199
I just used 0.3g of phenobarbital.

33
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,040
I followed Dr. Sun's prescription.

34
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,600
Are you sure?

35
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,010
Was the dosage correct?

36
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,760
That's impossible.

37
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,940
The doses were prepared beforehand.

38
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:23,040
Then why did the patient suddenly suffer heart failure?

39
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:23,800
Director.

40
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:26,240
I've been at the hospital for years.

41
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,160
You know my skills.

42
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,480
It really wasn't me.

43
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,850
I don't know what happened.

44
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,120
Director.

45
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,320
I really don't know what happened.

46
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,920
Director.

47
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,760
So you held a grudge

48
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,160
and killed Sun Yuyao.

49
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,240
I didn't mean to kill her.

50
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,960
I just wanted an explanation.

51
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:01,360
You're out now.

52
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,840
Why dwell on the past?

53
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,760
I just want to know

54
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:08,200
what exactly I did wrong.

55
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,800
There is no right or wrong.

56
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,260
Just accept your bad luck.

57
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:14,720
Bad luck?

58
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,600
I did six months in jail.

59
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,079
Just because of bad luck?

60
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,570
Should I go to jail instead?

61
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,520
How would I live my life then?

62
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,329
I'm heading out.

63
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,400
The movie is about to start.

64
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,400
You should leave.

65
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,760
Where should I go?

66
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,060
Why should I leave?

67
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,600
Don't I have a life to live?

68
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:35,560
What about me?

69
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,660
What about my life?

70
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,480
Don't I have a life to live?

71
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,520
Don't I have a life to live?

72
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,800
After I accidentally killed her,

73
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,460
I knew I couldn't stay in the Chinese territory.

74
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,010
So I hid in the Concessions.

75
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,960
Then why did you pretend to be Sun Yuyao?

76
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,760
Since I was in a new place,

77
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,840
why not start a new life?

78
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:14,880
If it were you,

79
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,760
would you still want to live

80
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:18,600
like a servant again?

81
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:21,200
But not just anyone

82
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,060
can be a doctor.

83
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:24,800
Isn't it just seeing patients and prescribing medicine?

84
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,800
How hard can it be?

85
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,600
I can learn.

86
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,840
Aren't you afraid something will go wrong?

87
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,040
As a doctor,

88
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,700
a bad reputation is the real problem.

89
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,720
He's been on this medicine for over two weeks,

90
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,250
and it hasn't helped at all.

91
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,360
Do you even know how to treat people?

92
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:43,040
Everyone's condition is different,

93
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,170
so the effects vary.

94
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,060
This is normal.

95
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,560
But it shouldn't be completely useless.

96
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,280
My husband has been lying here for so long,

97
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,480
and he hasn't improved a bit.

98
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,440
This is the only medicine for your husband's condition.

99
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:52,960
If he doesn't recover,

100
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,680
there's nothing I can do.

101
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:54,840
How can you say that?

102
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,120
Are you even a doctor?

103
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,880
If not, get us someone who is.

104
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,320
Yeah.

105
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,580
He hasn't improved in so long.

106
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,130
Probably not a real doctor.

107
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,160
No improvement after all this time.

108
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,400
Dr. Sun.

109
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,360
The patient in Bed 5 is critical.

110
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,730
Phenobarbital.

111
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,360
He's stable.

112
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,659
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

113
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,020
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

114
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,300
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

115
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,960
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

116
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,120
I'm so grateful.

117
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,400
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

118
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,960
Thank you, Dr. Sun.

119
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,800
Thank you.

120
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:03,800
Thank you.

121
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,640
You poison patients first,

122
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:06,840
then stage a rescue,

123
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:09,280
just to make people think you're a brilliant doctor.

124
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,520
Only then

125
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:12,160
will they thank me

126
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,600
and realize how important I am.

127
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,480
You're playing with human lives.

128
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:18,120
You're not fit to be a doctor.

129
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:21,540
From the moment they step into the hospital,

130
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:24,260
their lives no longer belong to them.

131
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,610
Even if it wasn't me,

132
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,280
they could be misdiagnosed

133
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:28,640
or given the wrong meds.

134
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:30,700
That's no excuse for poisoning them.

135
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,680
For your own selfish gain,

136
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:34,000
you treat human life as nothing.

137
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,600
Don't you have a conscience?

138
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,360
If I'm not mistaken,

139
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,940
Gu Zhiting didn't die of natural causes, did he?

140
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,360
Accidents do happen occasionally.

141
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,540
Occasionally?

142
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:53,159
Since you arrived at Guangren Hospital,

143
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,970
twenty-three people have died at your hands.

144
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,960
You call that occasionally?

145
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,440
See?

146
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,930
You're all the same.

147
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:13,400
You only blame me for my mistakes,

148
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,880
but never thank me for saving lives.

149
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:19,240
We...

150
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:23,900
You're really talking about Director Cao, aren't you?

151
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:26,560
I know.

152
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,240
You're going to say you didn't mean to kill him,

153
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,040
right?

154
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,960
Now that I am Sun Yuyao,

155
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:38,850
I can never go back to being Chen Yulan.

156
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,320
Doctor Sun,

157
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,800
you know I've always trusted you.

158
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,700
But with this booklet,

159
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,760
I really can't answer to the board.

160
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,060
Is there a problem?

161
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:56,800
You graduated from St. John's University.

162
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,040
This isn't up to your standard.

163
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,880
Your diploma

164
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,200
isn't fake, is it?

165
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,720
How is that possible?

166
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,480
Tell you what.

167
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,180
Go back for now.

168
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,400
Write me a report within three days.

169
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,220
Explain yourself.

170
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,280
Secretary Zhang.

171
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,760
Go to St. John's University tomorrow

172
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:26,890
and get a file for me.

173
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:28,880
Sun Yuyao's file.

174
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:29,880
Yes.

175
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:30,920
I want hers.

176
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,000
Okay.

177
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,840
Ten.

178
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,720
So you planned from the start

179
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,560
to frame Gu Zhang.

180
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,600
No.

181
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:47,120
It started the day you found him.

182
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,480
When I saw you outside his ward that day,

183
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:55,000
I knew you hadn't actually closed the case.

184
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:10,640
Given what Gu Zhang is like,

185
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,940
you'd dig up his dirt sooner or later.

186
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:17,080
I might as well take advantage of it.

187
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,540
He deserved to die anyway.

188
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:23,080
So you knew what kind of person he was all along.

189
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,760
I did more than just know.

190
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:28,000
Even without this incident,

191
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,690
I would've killed him eventually.

192
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,080
Dr. Sun.

193
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,450
What are you hiding?

194
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,640
Why did you show up

195
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,700
looking like this?

196
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:46,680
Aren't you afraid of being seen?

197
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,080
If I'm seen,

198
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,360
at most I'm just an impostor.

199
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,600
But you were discovered.

200
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,000
It was a matter of life and death.

201
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,800
Don't be nervous.

202
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,920
You did me such a huge favor.

203
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:15,120
How could I bite the hand that fed me?

204
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:20,720
What do you want?

205
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,050
It was only then that I realized

206
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,690
he was nothing but a scoundrel.

207
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,320
At first, I thought

208
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,520
he just wanted money for wine and women.

209
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,120
I didn't expect that every month,

210
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,580
he'd spend over a hundred yuan just on opium.

211
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,010
To fill that bottomless pit of his,

212
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:45,320
I even had to steal medicine from the hospital to sell.

213
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,360
Chen Yulan.

214
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:50,600
Do you know,

215
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:54,480
you were this close to successfully framing someone.

216
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,160
Do you remember Zhang Xiaojuan,

217
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,520
the nurse you used as a scapegoat?

218
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:04,440
She became a taxi dancer after being fired from the hospital.

219
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,520
On the night Director Cao was killed,

220
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,250
Gu Zhang was at her dance hall the whole night.

221
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,440
So that explains it.

222
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,120
Just now in the car,

223
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,560
I kept wondering

224
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:30,120
where exactly I gave myself away.

225
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:35,000
But how could Gu Zhang give up without a fight

226
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,130
and let you kill him?

227
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,560
Don't forget,

228
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,440
he's a drunkard.

229
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,000
Rickshaw.

230
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,170
Why did you drink so much again?

231
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:55,480
Give me a hand.

232
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,000
Healers are benevolent.

233
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,050
You've saved lives before.

234
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:25,020
Doesn't saving lives feel better than taking them?

235
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,800
Have you never thought about turning back?

236
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,760
Turn back?

237
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,400
How can I turn back?

238
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:40,400
From the moment I became Sun Yuyao,

239
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,800
I could only continue down this path.

240
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:46,920
Chen Yulan.

241
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,800
Let me ask you one last question.

242
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,840
Where did you bury Sun Yuyao?

243
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,820
The body is badly decomposed.

244
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:33,640
But this earring

245
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,260
matches the one in Sun Yuyao's photo.

246
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:47,500
Sun Yuyao's father is still looking for her, right?

247
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,920
Finding her is worse than not finding her.

248
00:16:50,680 --> 00:16:52,610
At least there would still be hope.

249
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,800
Qin Xin.

250
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:58,280
Sew Sun Yuyao's body up nicely.

251
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,280
Make their final goodbye

252
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,000
a bit more dignified.

253
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:41,440
Look.

254
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,580
Doesn't it look like snow?

255
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:06,920
Give me a hand.

256
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:17,840
Maybe we should seal it up.

257
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:19,290
It'll get dusty.

258
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:20,960
No.

259
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,200
And the installation fee.

260
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,440
You said I don't have to pay.

261
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,900
Don't go back on your word.

262
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,080
Don't worry.

263
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,480
I keep my word.

264
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,080
Before I leave here,

265
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,480
I'll pay for everything.

266
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,500
She's been sitting here for two days.

267
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,320
Why doesn't she go back and wait?

268
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,480
Zhang Dajiang.

269
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,280
Zhang Dajiang.

270
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,080
Zhang Dajiang.

271
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:52,120
Girls,

272
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:53,560
help me.

273
00:18:58,640 --> 00:18:59,800
Zhang Dajiang.

274
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,480
Zhang Dajiang.

275
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:06,080
My condolences.

276
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,520
Zhang Dajiang.

277
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,080
Zhang Dajiang.
